A.1 Entropy-Based Weighting
Entropy-based weighting assigns dynamic, input-dependent aggregation weights based on the predictive uncertainty of each model.
For a query input , let denote the output logits of model , and let be the corresponding predictive distribution. We quantify uncertainty using Shannon entropy:
Models with lower entropy are interpreted as being more confident. Accordingly, aggregation weights are defined via a softmax over negative entropy values:
